replies.text: @KillSh0tKD35 Install was not hard. Don't think it was in the video, but make sure you connect the USB adapter that comes with the screen if you want to upload music via USB or update the firmware in the future. I forgot to put mine in so had to find a different method to store my music since I did not want to exclusively stream music via Bluetooth (tedious to take apart and reinstall). Aside from that, install is straight forward and the product works as should. This video is a great tutorial! You won't have any issues.
replies.author: @TazZ243

replies.text: @TazZ243 where is the adapter plugged in?
replies.author: @luquie_curse

replies.text: @luquie_curse I guess I should say harness. It's provided with the screen. You'll see where to plug it in on the back of the Tesla screen. If you decide to plug in the USB harness, I believe you will need to figure out a way to run it from the back of the screen to the center console.
